If you pay less, it's illegal.
如果你付得更少，那就是违法的。

161
00:07:25,440 --> 00:07:28,760
And this is because we expect everyone to be treated fairly.
这是因为我们期望每个人都能得到公平对待。

162
00:07:28,760 --> 00:07:29,760
Right.
对。

163
00:07:29,760 --> 00:07:30,760
Right.
对。

164
00:07:30,760 --> 00:07:31,760
So it's not an advantage of people.
所以这不是对某些人的优势。

165
00:07:31,760 --> 00:07:32,760
No.
不是。

166
00:07:32,760 --> 00:07:37,840
And so, for example, in America, in my state, Illinois, I think the minimum wage is $7.25
所以，举个例子，在美国，我所在的州，伊利诺伊州，我认为最低工资是7.25美元

167
00:07:37,840 --> 00:07:38,840
per hour.
每小时。

168
00:07:38,840 --> 00:07:39,840
Oh, really?
哦，真的吗？

169
00:07:39,840 --> 00:07:40,840
Wow.
哇。

170
00:07:40,840 --> 00:07:41,840
It's pretty high.
这挺高的。

171
00:07:41,840 --> 00:07:44,800
And this is because people need to pay for health care and cars and houses and children.
这是因为人们需要支付医疗、汽车、房子和孩子的费用。

172
00:07:44,800 --> 00:07:49,640
So we say the least you can pay someone is $7.25.
所以我们说，你能付给别人的最低工资是7.25美元。

173
00:07:49,640 --> 00:07:50,640
Now this is different.
这就不一样了。

174
00:07:50,640 --> 00:07:53,600
As you said, it could be different from state to state.
就像你说的，各州可能不同。

175
00:07:53,600 --> 00:07:54,600
Right.
对。

176
00:07:54,600 --> 00:07:59,840
Because I know in some states, if I'm not mistaken, it's like $5.50 or something.
因为我知道有些州，如果我没记错的话，大概是5.50美元左右。

177
00:07:59,840 --> 00:08:01,520
Yeah, some states it's $5.
是啊，有些州是5美元。

178
00:08:01,520 --> 00:08:04,000
It depends on the cost of living.
这取决于生活成本。

179
00:08:04,000 --> 00:08:09,720
If it's cheap to rent an apartment or to find transportation, then obviously the minimum
如果租房或交通便宜，那么显然最低

180
00:08:09,720 --> 00:08:13,280
wage is going to be lower.
工资就会更低。

181
00:08:13,280 --> 00:08:15,000
Obviously there's no maximum wage.
显然没有最高工资。

182
00:08:15,000 --> 00:08:17,960
There's no number that is the most you can pay someone.
没有规定你能付给别人的最高金额。

183
00:08:17,960 --> 00:08:19,920
But all states have a minimum wage.
但所有州都有最低工资。

184
00:08:19,920 --> 00:08:23,880
It's the least that you can pay someone per hour.
这是你每小时能付给别人的最低金额。

185
00:08:23,880 --> 00:08:24,880
Okay.
好的。

186
00:08:24,880 --> 00:08:30,400
So for our last phrase, we don't know what the minimum wage is, we're not really sure
所以对于我们的最后一个短语，我们不知道最低工资是多少，我们不太确定

187
00:08:30,400 --> 00:08:32,000
what the going rate is.
现行行情是多少。

188
00:08:32,000 --> 00:08:37,240
So we should just negotiate with the person that answers the ad.
所以我们应该和回应广告的人协商。

189
00:08:37,240 --> 00:08:38,240
All right.
好的。

190
00:08:38,240 --> 00:08:40,840
Now to negotiate is a great verb.
现在，“协商”是一个很棒的动词。

191
00:08:40,840 --> 00:08:43,960
It is something that all of us do all the time.
这是我们所有人经常做的事情。

192
00:08:43,960 --> 00:08:49,480
So to negotiate means to try and compromise or to reach an agreement.
所以“协商”的意思是试图妥协或达成协议。

193
00:08:49,480 --> 00:08:55,160
So maybe I say the most I will pay is $11.
所以也许我说我最多付11美元。

194
00:08:55,160 --> 00:08:57,960
So I say, okay, I'll pay you $9.
所以我说，好吧，我付你9美元。

195
00:08:57,960 --> 00:09:00,600
And I say, no, I'll take 12.
然后我说，不，我要12美元。

196
00:09:00,600 --> 00:09:03,080
Yeah, sorry, 12 is too much.
是啊，抱歉，12美元太多了。

197
00:09:03,080 --> 00:09:04,640
I'll pay you 10.
我付你10美元。

198
00:09:04,640 --> 00:09:05,880
Okay, 11.
好吧，11美元。

199
00:09:05,880 --> 00:09:06,880
11?
11美元？

200
00:09:06,880 --> 00:09:07,880
Okay, agreed.
好的，成交。

201
00:09:07,880 --> 00:09:08,880
Okay.
好的。

202
00:09:08,880 --> 00:09:15,480
So it's a way of reaching an agreement, like you say, where both sides have their goals
所以这是一种达成协议的方式，就像你说的，双方都有自己的目标

203
00:09:15,480 --> 00:09:19,240
and they try to find a price that is the best for both parties.
他们试图找到一个对双方都最有利的价格。

204
00:09:19,240 --> 00:09:20,240
That's right.
没错。

205
00:09:20,240 --> 00:09:24,600
So it's basically a verb to negotiate and this is what you do, as you said, in many
所以这基本上是一个动词“协商”，正如你所说，你在很多

206
00:09:24,600 --> 00:09:27,560
circumstances, especially when you're getting a job.
情况下都会这样做，尤其是在找工作时。

207
00:09:27,560 --> 00:09:28,560
Yes.
是的。

208
00:09:28,560 --> 00:09:29,560
All right.
好的。

209
00:09:29,560 --> 00:09:38,920
So let's listen to the dialogue one last time and we'll be back in a bit.
那么让我们最后再听一遍对话，我们一会儿回来。

210
00:09:38,920 --> 00:09:40,800
Can you help me write a newspaper ad?
你能帮我写一则报纸广告吗？

211
00:09:40,800 --> 00:09:41,800
Sure.
当然。

212
00:09:41,800 --> 00:09:43,680
What are you looking to buy or sell?
你想买或卖什么？

213
00:09:43,680 --> 00:09:47,080
Actually, I want to hire someone to help me around the house.
实际上，我想雇个人帮我做家务。

214
00:09:47,080 --> 00:09:49,200
Oh, you want to get a maid?
哦，你想找个女佣？

215
00:09:49,200 --> 00:09:53,400
Well, I think it's better if you call her a cleaning lady or domestic help.
嗯，我觉得你最好称她为清洁工或家政帮手。

216
00:09:53,400 --> 00:09:54,400
Okay.
好的。

217
00:09:54,400 --> 00:09:56,360
So what do you want her to do?
那么你想让她做什么？

218
00:09:56,360 --> 00:09:57,840
Well, let's see.
嗯，让我想想。

219
00:09:57,840 --> 00:10:01,880
I want her to come in three times a week for a couple of hours to clean the kitchen, bathroom,
我想让她每周来三次，每次几个小时，打扫厨房、浴室，

220
00:10:01,880 --> 00:10:03,560
and maybe do some cooking.
也许再做点饭。

221
00:10:03,560 --> 00:10:04,560
Got it.
明白了。

222
00:10:04,560 --> 00:10:06,560
And how much do you offer per month?
那你每月付多少钱？

223
00:10:06,560 --> 00:10:07,760
I would pay her hourly.
我会按小时付钱。

224
00:10:07,760 --> 00:10:09,720
I don't know what the going rate is, though.
不过我不知道现行行情是多少。

225
00:10:09,720 --> 00:10:14,040
I know for sure it's more than minimum wage, but maybe you should just negotiate with the
我肯定这比最低工资高，但也许你应该和回应

226
00:10:14,040 --> 00:10:15,600
person that answers the ad.
广告的人协商一下。

227
00:10:15,600 --> 00:10:16,600
Great.
太好了。

228
00:10:16,600 --> 00:10:20,040
I'll be happy to help.
我很乐意帮忙。

229
00:10:20,040 --> 00:10:21,040
All right.
好的。

230
00:10:21,040 --> 00:10:26,600
So talking about minimum wage, is there any exception to why a person would earn less
那么说到最低工资，有没有什么例外情况，让人挣得

231
00:10:26,600 --> 00:10:27,680
than minimum wage?
比最低工资少？

232
00:10:27,680 --> 00:10:29,240
I don't believe so.
我不这么认为。

233
00:10:29,240 --> 00:10:32,200
Well, if they're not legally employed, right?
嗯，如果他们不是合法雇佣的，对吧？

234
00:10:32,200 --> 00:10:37,480
So if you're talking about people who we say are under the table, working under the table,
所以如果你说的是那些我们称为“打黑工”的人，也就是非法工作，

235
00:10:37,480 --> 00:10:39,760
that means that they're not working legally.
那就意味着他们不是合法工作。

236
00:10:39,760 --> 00:10:41,400
They're not paying taxes.
他们不交税。

237
00:10:41,400 --> 00:10:43,280
Then maybe those people will be paid less.
那么那些人可能拿到的工资会更低。

238
00:10:43,280 --> 00:10:45,120
What about waiters and waitresses?
那服务员和女服务员呢？

239
00:10:45,120 --> 00:10:49,760
I've heard that they earn less than minimum wage, but because they earn tips.
我听说他们挣得比最低工资少，因为他们有小费。

240
00:10:49,760 --> 00:10:50,760
This is true.
这是真的。

241
00:10:50,760 --> 00:10:58,440
So most restaurants say, okay, we will pay you as a waiter $3 an hour, but because you
所以大多数餐厅会说，好吧，我们作为雇主每小时付你3美元，但因为你

242
00:10:58,440 --> 00:11:02,240
will earn tips, you will earn more than the minimum wage.
会赚到小费，所以你的收入会高于最低工资。

243
00:11:02,240 --> 00:11:03,240
Right.
没错。

244
00:11:03,240 --> 00:11:04,600
So this is a good exception.
所以这是一个不错的例外情况。

245
00:11:04,600 --> 00:11:06,560
Unfortunately, there's no promise.
不幸的是，这没有保证。

246
00:11:06,560 --> 00:11:09,960
If you have no customers, you earn no tips, so you're still earning less than minimum
如果没有顾客，你就赚不到小费，那么你的收入仍然低于最低

247
00:11:09,960 --> 00:11:10,960
wage.
工资。

248
00:11:10,960 --> 00:11:11,960
That's right.
对。

249
00:11:11,960 --> 00:11:16,760
But if you have many, many customers and you earn lots of tips and you make $15 an hour
但如果顾客很多，你赚了很多小费，每小时能赚15美元

250
00:11:16,760 --> 00:11:19,360
or something much higher than the minimum wage.
或者比最低工资高得多。

251
00:11:19,360 --> 00:11:20,360
That's right.
没错。

252
00:11:20,360 --> 00:11:26,740
And actually being a waiter or a waitress is a very common job that a lot of people
实际上，当服务员是一份很常见的工作，很多人

253
00:11:26,740 --> 00:11:30,080
have when they're still in school or over the summer.
在上学或暑假期间都会做。

254
00:11:30,080 --> 00:11:36,440
And I've heard that it could be quite good because Americans are pretty good tippers.
我听说这工作还不错，因为美国人给小费挺大方的。

255
00:11:36,440 --> 00:11:37,440
That's right.
对。

256
00:11:37,440 --> 00:11:40,960
Americans generally tip between 15 and 20%.
美国人通常给15%到20%的小费。

257
00:11:40,960 --> 00:11:45,080
And you know that you have to tip because your waiter does not earn a minimum wage.
而且你知道必须给小费，因为服务员赚不到最低工资。

258
00:11:45,080 --> 00:11:46,080
Right.
没错。

259
00:11:46,080 --> 00:11:48,480
And so I think there is this expectation.
所以我觉得这是一种约定俗成的期望。

260
00:11:48,480 --> 00:11:54,120
So if your bill comes out to like a hundred bucks, then you are most definitely going
所以如果你的账单是100美元左右，那你肯定得

261
00:11:54,120 --> 00:11:56,560
to leave at least a $20 tip.
留下至少20美元的小费。

262
00:11:56,560 --> 00:12:00,320
Usually, yeah, 15 to $20, $20 if it's that much money.
通常是的，15到20美元，如果账单那么多的话就给20美元。

263
00:12:00,320 --> 00:12:01,320
Wow.
哇。

264
00:12:01,320 --> 00:12:02,320
Wow.
哇。

265
00:12:02,320 --> 00:12:06,280
That's very, very interesting, especially considering that in many countries, tipping
这非常非常有趣，尤其是考虑到在很多国家，小费

266
00:12:06,280 --> 00:12:12,920
is not really considered, it's not expected or it's not really something that people do.
并不被真正考虑，不是预期行为，也不是人们常做的事。

267
00:12:12,920 --> 00:12:13,920
Exactly.
确实如此。

268
00:12:13,920 --> 00:12:16,320
And in America, it is something that you have to do.
而在美国，这是你必须做的事。

269
00:12:16,320 --> 00:12:20,840
So I think a lot of times when people come to America, they don't expect to pay this.
所以我觉得很多时候，人们来美国时，没预料到要付这笔钱。

270
00:12:20,840 --> 00:12:22,480
There's tax, there's tip.
有税，还有小费。

271
00:12:22,480 --> 00:12:27,040
So when you see a menu, remember that the cost is a lot higher than you see.
所以当你看到菜单时，记住实际花费比你看到的要高得多。

272
00:12:27,040 --> 00:12:28,040
Exactly.
没错。

273
00:12:28,040 --> 00:12:29,040
All right.
好了。

274
00:12:29,040 --> 00:12:30,320
Very, very interesting topic.
非常非常有趣的话题。

275
